⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Miria, the Guardian
node TGL · TGL · ⟦Miria, the Guardian:TGL:ccd174⟧

WHO   — Miria, the Guardian — the defense android
WHAT  — The heroine of The Guardian Legend — who transforms between her humanoid Maiden form, exploring Naju's labyrinth, and a star-Fighter craft, blasting through its shoot-'em-up Corridors, to arm the alien world's self-destruct.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Naju is hurtling toward Earth full of monsters, and only the Guardian can get inside; because a machine built for one purpose will spend itself wholly on it; because a world must die so a world may live.
HOW   — By transformation — maiden to fighter and back — by the weapons and Chips she gathers in Naju's depths, and by defeating the boss that guards each of the ten safety devices until Naju's self-destruct is armed.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the Guardian — built for one world, sent to end another, and I will not turn back.

